text.comment: Default text color. if you don't know which color to pick for text, then this is the safest bet.

text-weak.comment:
Weak text color. 
Best used when there is regular neutral-text next to it.

text-disabled.comment:
Disabled text color. 
Only use for interactive elements in their disabled state.

text-inverted.comment:
Inverted text color. 
Only use on dark backgrounds.

background.comment: Default background color. If there's no reason for a semantic background, then that is the one to use.

background-medium.comment:
Medium contrasting background color. 

Ex: SubHeader

background-strong.comment:
Strongly contrasting background color. 
Use sparingly.

Ex: SubHeader back button.

background-disabled.comment:
Background color for disabled interactive elements only. 

Ex: Buttons

border-weak.comment:
Weaker border color, for discreet separators

Ex: Dividers

border-hover.comment:
Default border color, on mouseover. 

Ex: Inputs

border-disabled.comment:
Disabled border color for interactive elements 

Ex: Inputs

border-strong.comment:
Strongest border color.

Use on strong backgrounds (neutral-background-medium, -strong or -heavy).

icon-inverted.comment: Neutral icon color on dark backgrounds.

icon.comment:
Default icon color.

Best used when the icon doesn't expect interactivity.

icon-weak.comment:
Weakly contrasting icon color.

Best used when there is regular neutral-text or neutral-icon colors nearby for efficient hierarchy.

default.comment:
Chart color by default. 
If the chart only has one set of value, and not a semantic (danger / warning / success) then use this colorset.

default-weak.comment:
Chart color: default-weak.

default-strong.comment:
Chart color: default-strong.

default-hover.comment:
Chart color: default on mouseover for interactive charts.

if there is text on top if this, use default-text-weak.
